  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Measuring the quality of generated natural language presents several challenges due to the diverse range of generation methods and evaluation criteria (Gehrmann et al., 2023).",
    "The LLM-as-a-judge paradigm has recently emerged as a compelling approach to these evaluation challenges.",
    "By leveraging the reasoning capabilities of large language models (LLMs), this approach can provide more nuanced assessments that correlate better with human judgments across diverse tasks (Gu et al., 2025).",
    "LLM judges typically output both rationales and numeric scores, thus combining the comprehensiveness of human evaluation with the scalability of automated metrics.",
    "Recent studies highlight issues with LLM judges such as low alignment with human scores, miscalibration, score compression, high variance, prompt sensitivity, and leniency bias (Thakur et al., 2025; Wei et al., 2025)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Measuring the quality of generated natural language presents several challenges due to the diverse range of generation methods and evaluation criteria (Gehrmann et al., 2023).",
